<h2 align="center" style="color:#b57400; font-size:  
25px;"><b>RANIKHET, UTTARAKHAND</b></h2>

<p class="data" >A legend says that a Kumaoni queen was  
enchanted by this tiny hill paradise and it's in her honour  
that a palace was built here, thus the name, 'queen's land' .  
While no trace of the palace can be found today, but Ranikhet  
remains the same: captivating, abounding with flowers, trees  
and green meadows in the midst of heavenly Himalayan  
surroundings. <br>Interestingly, the nine-hole Ranikhet Golf  
Course is one of the highest in Asia and the rolling meadows of  
the course are breathtaking.</p>
